Install Python and Django

Creation of Django Project
	django-admin startproject MyProjects

Run Django Project Webserver
	python manage.py runserver

Creation of Django Application
	python manage.py startapp BookApp
	
Adding Application to Project
	Open settings.py from MyProjects -> INSTALLED_APPS -> 'BookApp'
	
Create View in BookApp
	Open views.py from BookApp 
		from django.shortcuts import render
		from django.http import HttpResponse 

		def welcome(request):
			message = '<h1> Welcome to Bookstore Management System</h1>'
			return HttpResponse(message)

Add View in URL pattern
	Open urls.py from MyProjects
		from django.contrib import admin
		from django.urls import path
		from BookApp import views

		urlpatterns = [
			path('admin/', admin.site.urls),
			path('welcome',views.welcome)
		]

Create new application TimeApp, Add to project, create view
	from django.shortcuts import render
	from django.http import HttpResponse 
	import datetime

	def showTime(request):
		time=datetime.datetime.now()
		return HttpResponse('<h1> The Time is :' + str(time) + '</h1>')
		
Add the TimeApp View in the URL Pattern
	from django.contrib import admin
	from django.urls import path
	from BookApp import views as v1
	from TimeApp import views as v2

	urlpatterns = [
		path('admin/', admin.site.urls),
		path('welcome',v1.welcome),
		path('showTime',v2.showTime)
	]

Create urls.py file in BookApp and TimeApp 
	BookApp -> urls.py
		from django.urls import path
		from BookApp import views

		urlpatterns = [
			path('welcome',views.welcome),
		]
	TimeApp -> urls.py
		from django.urls import path
		from TimeApp import views

		urlpatterns = [
			path('time',views.showTime)
		]
	MyProjects -> urls.py
		from django.contrib import admin
		from django.urls import include, path

		urlpatterns = [
			path('admin/', admin.site.urls),
			path('BookApp/', include('BookApp.urls')),
			path('TimeApp/', include('TimeApp.urls')),
		]

Rendering HTML files

Create templates/bookapp folder and templates/timeapp folders under MyProjects 
Open settings.py from MyProjects 
	from pathlib import Path
	import os

	# Build paths inside the project like this: BASE_DIR / 'subdir'.
	BASE_DIR = Path(__file__).resolve().parent.parent
	TEMPLATE_DIR = os.path.join(os.path.dirname(os.path.dirname(os.path.abspath(__file__))),'templates')

	TEMPLATES = [
		{
			'BACKEND': 'django.template.backends.django.DjangoTemplates',
			'DIRS': [TEMPLATE_DIR],
			'APP_DIRS': True,
			'OPTIONS': {
				'context_processors': [
					'django.template.context_processors.request',
					'django.contrib.auth.context_processors.auth',
					'django.contrib.messages.context_processors.messages',
				],
			},
		},
	]
	
